<br>
If you are OOM then you med x% faster... slowing down to normal as you get to full mana.<br>
<br>
The time it takes to med from 0 to full mana wouldn't change, just allows us to keep a decent DPS as we were OOM.<br>
<br>
This would only effect soloing mobs that we can kill with half a bar of mana.<br>
<br>
Would this unbalane some other part of the game?  Dunno.<br>
<br>
I was thinking this change could work on all casting classes.<br>
<br>
Barjam<br>
55 Wizard.<br>
Raptors suck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=booboo>BooBoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 19<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/7/02 11:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Variable meditation rates... this would rock.</span><hr size=1> Actually I think thats a great idea.  Say if a wizard stayed under 20% mana he would regen it enough to equal a monks total damage per hour.  Would make a wizard wanted in the normal xp groups at the penality if not having mana to burn adds or evac.  In a raid situation wizards would behave much like they do now.  Also, soloing wouldn't really be improved since you need most your mana bar to quad.<br>
<br>
Great idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubarjam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Barjam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/8/02 9:30 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Seems like most folks on here can figure out how to exploit just about any suggestion....  any ideas on how this might break the game?<br>
<br>
Barjam <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiznitch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Siznitch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 5:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> This would make us significantly better at root/nuke xping.  So to say that this would not improve our soloability, is not entirely accurate.<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=123170" target=_Blank">Siznitch</a><Br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=133412" target=_Blank">Squishnemall</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaniar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aniar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 812<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/15/02 2:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> This would be exploited just as much as warriors who keep themselves under 40% XP for the berzerker mode.<br>
<br>
if you want a &quot;variable mana regen&quot; idea that can't be exploited like this, have the faster regen happen when you're full, so you're less likely to burn it all off, and you get rewarded for staying fom, rather than being rewarded for being oom.<br>
<br>
Now, you could say, &quot;but when we're low on mana, we can't burn that additional add.&quot;  I'd respond - when we're low on mana, we can still root, the chanter can still mez. <p><center>
<img src="http://www.totalnetsolutions.net/nightwatch/images/aniar-sig.jpg" alt="Aniar Orrenson" hspace="10" vspace="10">
<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27902" target="_blank">Look down my pants with Magelo!</a>
</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=booboo>BooBoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/02 11:36 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Root and nuke at low mana would be improved but not to the point that its better then quad kiting.  Quad kiting you're getting around 10 damage per point of mana.  Even using a 4-1 nuke, you'll have to increase the lower half regen to 2.5x what it currently is.<br>
<br>
Only thing it would do for solo would be to make more areas viable for solo wizards to xp.  God forbid.<br>
<br>
Real reason I like this idea is that it increases wizards group value without increasing their solo ability, much..<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uelasto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elasto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/02 9:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> *nods* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufold.showPublicProfile?language=EN>fold</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/19/02 9:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I have recently thought it would be nice to make it so that if you med with the book open, you would regen mana faster than if you were just sitting there with the book closed. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=121085">Fold Flamtoss</a><BR>
Knights of Zek<BR>
56 Evoker <BR><BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49694"> Prysse Aslanian</a><BR>
32 Beastlord<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uraviennaridhol.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravienn Aridhol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 136<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/20/02 12:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
I have recently thought it would be nice to make it so that if you med with the book open, you would regen mana faster than if you were just sitting there with the book closed. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I like that idea.. it would work well in the risk vs reward category that seems to prevail in the game.<br>
<br>
Zach <p><p align=center><a href=http://www.geocities.com/bowrathe><IMG SRC=http://www.mygem.net/bloodofwar/imagesP/ravsig.jpg border=0 height=203 width=515>
</a></p>
<BR>
<P ALIGN=CENTER> "Talking to you is like a Martian talking to a Fungo"--Crash Davis, Bull Durham--</P>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unaanaaneebooboo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Naanaan Eebooboo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 350<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/20/02 5:36 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I agree that it should be reversed... the nearer you are to FM, the faster your manaregen should be. Prevents soloing, results in better DPS in groups.<br>
<br>
Of course, all we'll have to do is unequip all our int and mana equipment when we get LoM. Manapool gets shrinked to 60%, manaregen goes up. Soon as mana reaches 90%, start equipping int + mana stuff one by one, till we get FM again.<br>
<br>
Oh well. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uznailvh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Znail vh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/21/02 8:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> Any exploits with removing int gear can easily be fixed by making the meditation bonus to be simply linked to your current mana. That way also giving a bonus for having more int. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uetelka.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Etelka</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/22/02 8:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I like this one!<br>
That would also mean that your Int influences your damage over time. It always irritated me that more Int for a caster, contrary to more Str for a melee, did not really influence the amount of damage you could do, only the length of time you can keep that damage up. This way, more Int would raise the damage you can do in, say, an hour.<br>
You have to be a bit prudent in mana management, which I like as well: if you want to play an Int-class, you'd better be smart yourself. Anything that rewards smart playing has my vote. <p><img src="http://home.wxs.nl/~tom.van.der.veen/Sig-custom.jpg" border="0">
